[ctns_make id='axClosureQ2-2']

    [ctns_question style='width:70%;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;']
The set of integers is closed under multiplication.
    [/ctns_question]
    
    [ctns_right style='width:70%;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;']
The product $$a \cdot b$$ is itself an integer for any two integers $$a$$ and $$b$$.
    [/ctns_right]

    [ctns_wrong style='width:70%;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;']
The question asks whether the product of any two integers is itself a integer. To understand what this question is asking, try adding together pairs of integers to see whether you can find a pair of numbers whose product is not a integer.
    [/ctns_wrong]
    
    [ctns_undecided style='width:70%;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;']
The question asks whether the product of any two integers is itself a integer. To understand what this question is asking, try adding together pairs of integers to see whether you can find a pair of numbers whose product is not a integer.
    [/ctns_undecided]
    
[/ctns_make]
